node.text:
The last time two teenagers met in the final of a tennis grand slam was at the 1999 #USOpen, when a 17-year-old Serena Williams beat 18-year-old Martina Hingis to the title - her first singles grand slam victory!⁠⁠
⁠⁠
Ahead of Emma Raducanu and Leylah Fernandez's all-teenager showdown at this year's tournament, enjoy these vintage snaps from '99! 😍⁠⁠
⁠⁠
Hit the link in bio for more info!
